.\" Man page for unpin. Hand-written man(7) roff; embedded into the unpin
.\" binary as a unpin/man/unpin.1 ZIP entry by the nix build (flake.nix
.\" withUnpinMan) and read back by `unpin man` (see docs/embedded-metadata.md).
.TH UNPIN 1 "2026" "unpin" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
unpin \- install single-binary CLI tools straight from GitHub releases
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B unpin
.RI [ COMMAND ]
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ PKG ...]
.br
.B unpin
.I owner/repo
.RB [ @ \fIversion\fR ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B unpin
downloads prebuilt, single-file executables from GitHub releases and links
them onto your
.BR PATH \(em
no root, no distribution package manager, and no
.I /nix/store
closure at runtime. Each installed tool is one executable per OS, with no
companion DLL, dylib, or shared object.
.PP
Packages are addressed as
.IR owner/repo .
A bare
.I name
is shorthand for
.IR unpins/ name ,
the curated catalog. A version may be pinned with
.RI @ version
(for example
.BR unpins/jq@1.7.1 ).
.PP
If the first argument is not a known command, it is treated as a package to
.BR run ,
so
.B unpin owner/repo
is equivalent to
.BR "unpin run owner/repo" .
Installing onto
.B PATH
is the explicit
.BR "unpin install" .
This also dispatches helper verbs to their packages: with no
.B man
command built in,
.B unpin man coreutils ls
runs the
.I man
package (a patched mandoc) on coreutils' embedded manual.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI install " [PKG...]"
Install one or more packages from GitHub releases onto
.BR PATH .
With no
.IR PKG ,
unpin installs itself: it moves the running binary into place and adds it to
.BR PATH .
.TP
.BI update " [NAME...]"
Update one, several, or (with no arguments) all installed packages.
.TP
.BI uninstall " [NAME...]"
Uninstall one, several, or (with no arguments, after confirmation) all
installed packages.
.TP
.B list
List installed packages.
.TP
.BI info " PKG..."
Show details about one or more packages, installed or remote.
.TP
.B clean
Remove dangling links and unused version directories from the unpin cache.
.TP
.BI run " PKG " [ \fB\-\-\fR " ARG..." ]
Run a package's binary without installing it; no entry is added to
.BR PATH .
This is the default command, so the
.B run
keyword may be omitted. Arguments after
.B \-\-
are forwarded to the binary.
A cached version is run directly without contacting GitHub; pass
.B \-\-refresh
to re-resolve the latest release.
.TP
.BI completion " SHELL"
Print a shell completion script for
.IR bash ", " zsh ", " fish ", or " elvish .
.TP
.BI bundle " list|dump PKG " [ \fIENTRY\fR ]
Inspect a package's embedded metadata bundle \(em its
.I unpin/*
entries. A stable interface used by helper packages such as
.IR man .
.SH OPTIONS
These apply to
.B install
and
.B update
unless noted.
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip prompts (assume yes).
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Re-download and re-link even when the latest cached version is already
installed. On self-install this just refreshes the placed binary and its
.B PATH
link.
.TP
.B \-\-refresh
Re-resolve the latest release from GitHub instead of running a cached version
.RB ( run " only)."
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-jobs " \fIN\fR"
Number of parallel downloads (default: min(N, 4)).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-pick
Always prompt to choose the release asset instead of auto-picking.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Print every HTTP request and show release assets that were filtered out.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-data
Skip the per-release runtime-data tarball (overrides config
.IR data ).
.TP
.B \-\-aliases
Install multi-call aliases declared by a catalog package.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-aliases
Skip multi-call aliases (wins over
.B \-\-aliases
and
.BR \-\-ask\-aliases ).
.TP
.B \-\-ask\-aliases
Prompt before installing aliases.
.SH CONFIGURATION
A flat
.I key = value
file with
.B #
comments. Recognized keys:
.TP
.BI http_timeout " seconds"
Per-request HTTP timeout (default: 30).
.TP
.BI use_gh_auth " true|false"
Shell out to
.B gh auth token
for the GitHub token (default: false).
.TP
.BI data " true|false"
Download the per-release runtime-data tarball (default: true).
.TP
.BI aliases " yes|no|ask"
Install multi-call aliases declared by catalog packages (default: yes).
Non-catalog
.I owner/repo
installs always skip aliases.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.BR GITHUB_TOKEN ", " GH_TOKEN
GitHub API token. Raises the rate limit from 60 to 5000 requests per hour.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project home:
.UR https://unpins.org
.UE .
.SH BUGS
Report issues at
.UR https://github.com/unpins/unpin
.UE .
